<plot>A touching and breathtaking drama by the prize-winning film duo director Anette Skåhlberg and scriptwriter Martin Lima de Faria with the "Guldbagge"awarded Lia Boysen and Anders Ekborg in the leading parts. The film deals with the urge of being loved for who you are and not for what you do. Pablo looks up to his Daddy, but when Daddys idol Picasso dies a summers day in 1973, Daddys grief and anger is directed towards the family and Pablos Mum. One day Pablo sees bruises on his Mums arm...But how easy is it to stand up against Daddy when you are only 8 years old?"</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?422638</url></doc>
